@startuml UDP vs RUDP Header Comparison
skinparam defaultFontName Consolas
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam padding 4
skinparam map {
  BackgroundColor<<udp>> #E3F2FD
  BackgroundColor<<rudp>> #FFF3E0
}

title **Standard UDP Header  vs  Project RUDP Header**\nFull field-by-field comparison

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  UDP HEADER
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

map "**Standard UDP Header — 8 bytes**\n//RFC 768 · Transport Layer (Layer 4)//" as UDP <<udp>> {
  Byte 0-1  (16 bit) => **Source Port** — sender's port number
  Byte 2-3  (16 bit) => **Destination Port** — receiver's port number
  Byte 4-5  (16 bit) => **Length** — header (8B) + payload size
  Byte 6-7  (16 bit) => **Checksum** — optional in IPv4, covers header + payload + pseudo-header
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  RUDP HEADER
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

map "**Project RUDP Header — 14 bytes**\n//Custom · Application Layer · rides inside UDP payload//" as RUDP <<rudp>> {
  Byte 0-3   (32 bit) => **Sequence Number** — identifies each packet for ordering & retransmission
  Byte 4-7   (32 bit) => **Ack Number** — confirms receipt up to this seq, enables selective retransmit
  Byte 8     (8 bit)  => **Flags** — SYN(0x01) ACK(0x02) FIN(0x04) DATA(0x08) RST(0x10) PING(0x20) MSG_END(0x40)
  Byte 9     (8 bit)  => **Window** — sliding window size (default 8), receiver-side flow control
  Byte 10-11 (16 bit) => **Payload Length** — exact byte count of the JSON payload that follows
  Byte 12-13 (16 bit) => **CRC-16** — CRC-16/CCITT-FALSE over header[0:12] + payload, mandatory integrity
  Byte 14+   (variable) => **Payload** — JSON exam data (exam content, answers, sync metadata)
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  COMPARISON
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

map "**Feature Comparison**" as CMP {
  Reliable Delivery =>  UDP: **No** — fire and forget \n RUDP: **Yes** — seq/ack + retransmission on timeout
  Ordering =>  UDP: **No** — packets may arrive out of order \n RUDP: **Yes** — seq number enforces in-order delivery
  Flow Control =>  UDP: **No** — sender can flood receiver \n RUDP: **Yes** — sliding window (window field, default 8)
  Connection Lifecycle =>  UDP: **No** — connectionless \n RUDP: **Yes** — SYN/SYN-ACK/ACK handshake, FIN teardown, RST abort
  Integrity Check =>  UDP: **Optional** — checksum can be zero in IPv4 \n RUDP: **Mandatory** — CRC-16/CCITT over header + payload, packet rejected on mismatch
  Message Reassembly =>  UDP: **No** — one datagram = one message \n RUDP: **Yes** — MSG_END flag marks last chunk of multi-packet message
  Keepalive =>  UDP: **No** \n RUDP: **Yes** — PING flag for liveness detection
  Addressing =>  UDP: **Yes** — src/dst port in header \n RUDP: **No** — relies on underlying UDP ports for addressing
  Header Size =>  UDP: **8 bytes** \n RUDP: **14 bytes** (+ 8B UDP = 22B total overhead)
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  WHY RUDP
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

note as WHY
  **Why RUDP over plain UDP?**
  The exam system needs **reliable, ordered delivery** of questions
  and answers — but TCP's congestion control and head-of-line
  blocking add unwanted latency for synchronized delivery.

  RUDP gives us:
  1. **Reliability** without TCP's congestion window ramp-up
  2. **Custom flow control** tuned for exam traffic (window=8)
  3. **CRC-16 integrity** that is always enforced (not optional)
  4. **Connection management** (SYN/FIN) for clean session lifecycle
  5. **MSG_END reassembly** for large JSON payloads split across packets
  6. **PING keepalive** to detect disconnected exam clients quickly

  **Why not just TCP?**
  TCP is also used in this project (tcp-sync / tcp-nosync modes)
  as a **baseline for comparison**. The three transport modes
  (rudp-sync, tcp-sync, tcp-nosync) let us measure how each
  protocol affects synchronized exam delivery.
end note

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  ENCAPSULATION
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

note as STACK
  **Packet Encapsulation (wire format)**

  |= Layer |= Protocol |= Header |= Size |
  | Network | IP | IP Header | 20B |
  | Transport | UDP | Src/Dst Port + Len + Checksum | 8B |
  | Application | RUDP | Seq + Ack + Flags + Win + Len + CRC | 14B |
  | Data | JSON | Exam payload | var |
  | | | **Min total overhead** | **42B** |
end note

UDP -[hidden]-> RUDP
RUDP -[hidden]-> CMP
CMP -[hidden]-> WHY
WHY -[hidden]-> STACK

@enduml
